On Wed, Aug 20, 2003 at 10:44:05AM -0400, Oohvwbus(-at-)aol.com wrote:
> Well I changed out my cold start vavle, It was toast (literaly
> burned up),  the screw were loose and looked as if it leaking fuel
> on the manifold.  Anyway, my question is, since my bus won't start
> still,  Can i check my timing eventhough the bus isn't running?
> tonight I am going to adjust valves and attempt setting points,
> Never done this before.  Pretty EZ?

If you have the muir book it covers using a test light to set the
timing. This process and setting the point gap with feeler gauges will
be good enough to get it started. Just be sure to do a dynamic check
after you get it running.

